  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Protection Mechanisms in Poland Following the Crisis in Ukraine</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to strengthen and improve the protection mechanisms in Poland for persons fleeing Ukraine as a result of the crisis following the Russian invasion in late February 2022. Beneficiaries&apos; safety, dignity and well-being will be ensured, as IOM is supporting affected populations in Poland with accessing a broad range of comprehensive assistance, including direct protection assistance, provision of safe sanitation/living conditions and access to available services in Poland. Moreover, through IOM&apos;s Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) tools and methodology, information on the movement routes, intentions and needs of the persons fleeing into Poland are being collected and disseminated with relevant stakeholders to improve the protection response. With a view to mitigating protection risks and vulnerabilities of persons during their stay in Poland, comprehensive information and support will be also provided to facilitate their access to the labour market and associated livelihood opportunities. Lastly, in coordination with relevant national authorities, IOM is supporting the urgent evacuation of children at-risk, having crossed from Ukraine to Poland, into safe care arrangements in Greece. IOM is working closely with national/local authorities and stakeholders to coordinate the response and hence maximize the relevance and effectiveness of its interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
